The Health Ministry says in its latest data release shows that the recovery rate from coronavirus has increased to 90%. It says this is one of the better recovery rates in the world. The Ministry also added that another 1 268 people have tested positive for the coronavirus – bringing the total number of cases to 670 766. Twenty-two more deaths have been recorded – taking the overall death toll from COVID-19 to 16 398. Professor Bulie Magula on SA’s latest Covid-19 related deaths: #HealthcareHeroes Restrictions have been eased, but healthcare workers urge all South Africans to be mindful of the #Covid19 precautionary measures.
